Html:
Hey. I am new to this control (but loving it very much).<br />
<br />
I have a map (called googleMap). When I use the mouse scroll wheel to change zoom level it works fine. I also have a button on the form that will zoom in and one that will zoom out. I have those set to increment zoom by 1 (+= 1 or -= 1). Those work fine.<br />
<br />
What I am trying to accomplish is to allow a finer level of zooming (if possible). So I have written it so that if the Control key is pressed then the zoom level increment is smaller.<br />
<br />
It appears to work but the map isn't changing it's zoom level. So I had it write the zoom level each time it was incremented. The zoom level is changed but the map doesn't zoom in. Until I click the button for the sixth time. <br />
<br />
I understand this sounds confusing. Here is my button code:<br />
<pre><code>private void button1_Click(object sender, EventArgs e)
        {
            try
            {
                if (Control.ModifierKeys == Keys.Control)
                {
                    googleMap.Zoom += 0.2;
                }
                else
                {
                    googleMap.Zoom += 1;
                }
                Console.WriteLine(googleMap.Zoom);                
            }
            catch (Exception ex)
            {
                                MessageBox.Show(&quot;Screw Up:&quot; + Environment.NewLine + &quot;Message: &quot; + ex.Message);                
            }
        }</code></pre>

Now, here is the output from that Console.WriteLine:<br />
11<br />
12<br />
12.2<br />
12.4<br />
12.6<br />
12.8<br />
13<br />
13.2<br />
<br />
So initially I was at a zoom level of 10. I clicked the button (without Control key pressed) and that changed to the 11 (and the map zoomed). I clicked again (still no Control key pressed) and the zoom changed to 12 and the map zoomed.<br />
<br />
Then I held down the control key and clicked the button 6 times (as you can see from the output). It wasn't until the 6th click (13.2) that the map zoomed in again.<br />
<br />
Can the zoom level only increment by 1 (or greater)? Or am I just screwing something up? I tend to think it's the second and that I'm doing it incorrectly.<br />
